Description: Bruegel: Woman taken in Adultery. The connection of the engraving by [Pieter] Perret (Bastelaer III) with Rembrandt's drawing in Stockholm, [Otto] Benesch, [The Drawings of Rembrandt, London: Phaidon Press], vol. V, (1957), N° 1038, Figure 1253, observed by [J.L.A.A.M. van] Rijckevorsel, Rembrandt en de traditie [Rotterdam: Brusse],1932, p. 185, Fig. 233 (check) and Benesch. Benesch dates c. 1658-9. Look up Benesch, 2nd edition. There is the same wall of figures - no spatial depth though the woman herself and other details differ. Christ has become the central figure, with whom the woman is not competing.
